Here are a few of the winners and losers . Winners Richard Cordray : The Democrat was often knocked for being a boring gubernatorial candidate . Among his critics was the cleveland.com/Plain Dealer editorial board , which endorsed his chief primary opponent , Dennis Kucinich , in part , for the energy the former Cleveland mayor would bring to the governor 's office . Cordray 's personality is certainly more akin to that of financial planner than a party planner , but his ties to party leaders , unions and his fundraising were far too much for the more kinetic Kucinich . Cordray won more than 60 percent of the statewide vote and carried 86 out of Ohio 's 88 counties , including Kucinich 's base in Cuyahoga County . ( Joe Schiavoni won Trumbull and Mahoning counties . ) In November , however , Cordray 's personality shortcomings may be a larger liability for the uninspiring Democratic ticket , which fell short of turnout goals on Tuesday . Republican establishment : Ohio may have gone big for outsider Donald Trump in 2016 , but the 2018 primary showed Republican voters still favor more mainstream candidates , most notably Ohio Attorney General Mike DeWine ....
